# E-Commerce Business Analysis — SQL Project

## Overview
A complete business analysis project built entirely in SQL using
PostgreSQL. Covers 10 real business queries from basic aggregations
to advanced window functions and CTEs on a retail orders database.

## Tools Used
- PostgreSQL 16
- pgAdmin 4

## Database Structure
3 tables created from scratch:

customers table — customer_id, customer_name, city, state, segment

products table — product_id, product_name, category, sub_category

orders table — order_id, customer_id, product_id, order_date,
               quantity, discount, sales, profit, region

## 10 Business Queries Written

| Query | Business Question Answered |
|---|---|
| Query 1 | Total sales, profit, orders and profit margin |
| Query 2 | Sales and profit breakdown by category |
| Query 3 | Top 5 customers by total revenue |
| Query 4 | Monthly sales trend over time |
| Query 5 | Region wise performance comparison |
| Query 6 | Discount impact on profit using subquery |
| Query 7 | Running total sales using Window Function |
| Query 8 | Customer ranking by spend using RANK() |
| Query 9 | Loss making products using CTE |
| Query 10 | Customer segment comparison using advanced CTE |

## SQL Concepts Used
- SELECT with WHERE, ORDER BY, LIMIT
- JOIN — connecting customers, products and orders tables
- GROUP BY with aggregate functions SUM, COUNT, AVG
- Subqueries — inline derived tables
- CASE WHEN — conditional logic inside queries
- CTE — Common Table Expressions using WITH clause
- Window Functions — SUM OVER, RANK with PARTITION BY
- DISTINCTCOUNT and COUNTROWS

## Key Business Insights
- Technology category has highest profit margin
- Products with discount above 25 percent become loss making
- Corporate segment generates highest revenue per customer
- Month of December has highest sales across all regions

## How to Run
1. Install PostgreSQL free from postgresql.org
2. Open pgAdmin and create a new database called ecommerce_db
3. Open Query Tool
4. Copy and paste the ecommerce_analysis.sql file contents
5. Run each section one by one from top to bottom
